<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1431,2033]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">
Remark: The generic placement of this species is quite dubious. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gozmany, L. A." box="[989,1182,1827,1853]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" refId="ref9987" refString="Gozmany, L. A. (1978) Lecithoceridae. In: Amsel, H. G., Gregor, F. &amp; Reisser, H. (Eds.), Microlepidoptera Palaearctica. Vol. 5. Georg Fromme and Co., Wien, pp. 1 - 306." type="book" year="1978">Gozmány (1978)</bibRefCitation>
studied the species in 
<taxonomicName authority="Gozmany, 1978" authorityName="Gozmany" authorityYear="1978" box="[246,583,1863,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Catacreagra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[246,388,1864,1890]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Catacreagra</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gozmany, L. A." box="[399,583,1863,1889]" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" refId="ref9987" refString="Gozmany, L. A. (1978) Lecithoceridae. In: Amsel, H. G., Gregor, F. &amp; Reisser, H. (Eds.), Microlepidoptera Palaearctica. Vol. 5. Georg Fromme and Co., Wien, pp. 1 - 306." type="book" year="1978">Gozmány, 1978</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Wu &amp; Park (1999) synonymized the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gozmany" authorityYear="1978" box="[1111,1253,1864,1890]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Catacreagra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1111,1253,1864,1890]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Catacreagra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1925" box="[246,357,1899,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Carodista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[246,357,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="62">Carodista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but didn’t mention the status of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
